President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Tennessee due to severe storms, tornadoes, winds, and flooding that occurred from April 25-28, 2011. This declaration allows for federal aid to assist in the recovery efforts. Affected individuals in the counties of Bradley, Greene, Hamilton, and Washington can receive assistance such as grants for temporary housing, home repairs, and low-cost loans for uninsured property losses. Federal funding is also available for debris removal, emergency protective measures, and hazard mitigation measures on a cost-sharing basis. W. Montague Winfield has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional counties and forms of assistance may be designated after further assessments. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by calling the toll-free numbers provided. Further information can be obtained from FEMA.